WEBVTT

00:02.769 --> 00:05.437
             [♪♪♪]

00:08.009 --> 00:09.241
               [YAWNS]

00:10.311 --> 00:11.943
               Oh, boy.

00:14.581 --> 00:16.781
             Uh, Jeannie.

00:16.817 --> 00:18.217
          Jeannie, bedtime.

00:18.252 --> 00:19.585
           Bottle time.

00:19.620 --> 00:21.787
You're going to bed
so early, master?

00:21.822 --> 00:23.154
            Huh?
          Oh, yes.

00:23.190 --> 00:24.623
Yeah, I got
a rough day tomorrow.

00:24.658 --> 00:26.792
Those, uh, Russian
cosmonauts are coming in.

00:26.827 --> 00:29.194
   Ah. Have a good
   sleep, master.

00:29.229 --> 00:30.796
   I am going out.

00:30.831 --> 00:32.197
You're going out?
Where?

00:32.232 --> 00:33.365
                I have a date.

00:33.400 --> 00:34.933
              Captain Healey
          is going to pick me up

00:34.969 --> 00:36.301
                 in front
          of the public library.

00:36.336 --> 00:38.003
Now, now, wait a minute.
We've be--

00:38.038 --> 00:39.270
Been all through this before.

00:39.306 --> 00:41.139
You-- You can't go out
with Captain Healey.

00:41.174 --> 00:43.609
He's turned in his wolf suit.
Ha-ha. He wants to marry you.

00:43.644 --> 00:45.811
                  Hm. I know.
Yeah, well, he can't.

00:45.846 --> 00:47.546
                     Why not?
                   I am single.

00:47.581 --> 00:48.580
  Yeah, well...

00:48.616 --> 00:50.448
you've been single
for 2000 years.

00:50.484 --> 00:51.683
          Well, that is just it.

00:51.719 --> 00:53.251
             I do not wish to be
                an old maid.

00:53.286 --> 00:54.452
All right,
look, Jeannie.

00:54.488 --> 00:56.655
I-I can't let you do this
to my best friend.

00:56.690 --> 00:57.689
    Uh--

00:57.725 --> 00:59.324
  He's only read
  Omar Khayyám.

00:59.359 --> 01:01.493
You used to sit in his tent
and drink wine with him.

01:01.529 --> 01:04.262
  Well, I would not be going out
       with your best friend

01:04.297 --> 01:06.398
             if I was married
            to <i> his</i> best friend.

01:06.433 --> 01:09.034
Yes. Jeannie, we've been
through that too.

01:09.069 --> 01:10.535
              Oh, there would be
                many advantages

01:10.570 --> 01:12.037
         to being married to me,
                 master.

01:12.072 --> 01:13.372
            For instance:

01:15.476 --> 01:17.676
   Huh? Really?

01:17.711 --> 01:18.844
  [BOTH LAUGHING]

01:18.879 --> 01:21.780
What are you
trying to prove?

01:21.815 --> 01:23.715
       Well, this is the biggest
           advantage of all.

01:23.750 --> 01:25.617
         When you are old,
    I will still look like this,

01:25.652 --> 01:27.920
       and you will not have to
           chase young girls.

01:27.955 --> 01:29.621
    Huh? Oh.
    Ah! Ah!

01:29.656 --> 01:30.989
        [BOTH LAUGHING]

01:35.061 --> 01:37.328
All right, Jeannie. I'm aware
of the fringe benefits.

01:37.364 --> 01:38.931
     But I'm not ready
    to get married yet.

01:40.234 --> 01:41.200
                  [SIGHS]
               Oh, very well.

01:41.235 --> 01:42.467
               I have waited
              for 2000 years.

01:42.502 --> 01:44.436
            I suppose I can wait
              a while longer.

01:44.471 --> 01:46.004
   Well, sure you can.
     In the meantime,

01:46.039 --> 01:47.906
     you won't go out
with Captain Healey, right?

01:47.941 --> 01:49.708
      If it will make you happy.

01:49.743 --> 01:50.742
            And if you promise

01:50.777 --> 01:52.377
              not to go out
            with other girls.

01:52.412 --> 01:53.711
       Right.
   No other girls?

01:53.747 --> 01:55.213
    I'm a bachelor.
  Of course I'll go--

01:55.249 --> 01:56.748
                Goodbye, master.
   You got a deal.

01:58.519 --> 02:00.252
          In that case...

02:03.457 --> 02:04.756
           [GIGGLES]

02:09.262 --> 02:10.762
            Good night, master.

02:13.767 --> 02:15.266
                     [YAWNS]

02:24.678 --> 02:25.844
    Even if I did marry her,

02:25.879 --> 02:27.479
        how would I ever
       get in that bottle?

02:30.183 --> 02:32.284
             [♪♪♪]

03:17.398 --> 03:19.898
             [♪♪♪]

03:25.105 --> 03:27.439
             [♪♪♪]

03:38.552 --> 03:39.551
            [INAUDIBLE DIALOGUE]

03:43.824 --> 03:45.290
 The general will be
   right with you.

03:45.325 --> 03:46.324
            Thank you,
             sergeant.

03:49.062 --> 03:50.796
            Tony, you've got to
           help me find Jeannie.

03:50.831 --> 03:52.697
              She vanished
          into thin air again.

03:52.733 --> 03:54.332
Well, I don't know
what I can do, Roge.

03:54.367 --> 03:56.000
                 I see her once
               and d-disappears.

03:56.036 --> 03:58.837
       A woman just can't vanish
         into a puff of smoke.

03:58.872 --> 04:01.406
Roger, with women,
logic will get you nowhere.

04:01.442 --> 04:03.308
          Well, I'll tell you,
       I got-- I gotta find her.

04:03.343 --> 04:05.076
                I'm going crazy.
                 You see this...

04:05.111 --> 04:06.311
                   Look at that.
                   Isn't that--?

04:06.346 --> 04:07.846
           TONY:
Hey, that's a lot of carats.

04:07.881 --> 04:09.647
           I was gonna put it
       on her finger last night,

04:09.682 --> 04:10.916
           but what does she do?

04:10.951 --> 04:13.017
       She stands me up in front
         of the public library.

04:13.053 --> 04:15.253
Well, if you want my advice,
you forget her.

04:15.288 --> 04:17.221
       I don't want your advice.
            I want Jeannie.

04:19.593 --> 04:20.658
    Good morning, gentlemen.

04:20.694 --> 04:23.361
        TONY: Good morning, sir.
              ROGER: General.

04:23.396 --> 04:25.731
The Russian cosmonauts
are with Dr. Bellows now.

04:25.766 --> 04:28.066
They'll join us
in a moment.

04:28.102 --> 04:31.903
The State Department has invited
Majors Posnofsky and Tiomkin

04:31.939 --> 04:34.072
here as a gesture
of good will.

04:34.107 --> 04:36.574
 They'll be staying at my hotel
         for two days.

04:36.610 --> 04:38.876
     You gentlemen will be
their hosts and entertain them.

04:38.912 --> 04:41.779
Uh, what type of entertainment
would you suggest, sir?

04:41.815 --> 04:43.215
Their stay
will be brief,

04:43.250 --> 04:46.718
  but we'd like them to leave
   impressed with the flavor

04:46.754 --> 04:49.755
        and the majesty
     of our great country.

04:49.790 --> 04:52.190
       So keep them away
    from the Watusi festival

04:52.225 --> 04:53.424
     and the strip joints.

04:55.528 --> 04:56.594
    Good morning, gentlemen.

04:56.630 --> 04:57.695
              Good morning, sir.

04:57.730 --> 04:58.763
ROGER:
Colonel.

05:03.236 --> 05:05.370
    Captain Nelson,
    Captain Healey.

05:05.405 --> 05:07.539
      Major Tiomkin
   and Major Posnofsky.

05:07.574 --> 05:08.640
                 How do you do?

05:08.675 --> 05:10.909
     [SPEAKING IN RUSSIAN]

05:10.944 --> 05:12.243
                Thank you.

05:12.279 --> 05:14.412
 Captain Healey and Capt. Nelson
        will do everything

05:14.447 --> 05:15.881
               to make your stay
                a pleasant one.

05:15.916 --> 05:17.215
Captain
Healey,

05:17.251 --> 05:19.884
             you'll be in charge
             of Major Posnofsky.

05:20.854 --> 05:22.754
                 Captain Nelson,
                  Major Tiomkin.

05:22.789 --> 05:24.289
             My pleasure, major.

05:24.324 --> 05:25.790
    Mine too.

05:25.826 --> 05:27.959
                 GENERAL:
         I think it's about time

05:27.995 --> 05:30.028
 for our tour around the base,
      right, Dr. Bellows?

05:30.063 --> 05:31.796
  The photographers
 are waiting outside.

05:31.832 --> 05:32.964
        Right
      this way.

05:33.000 --> 05:34.766
         The press has been
             swarming

05:34.801 --> 05:36.434
              for an interview
            with you cosmonauts.

05:36.469 --> 05:37.569
                      [TALKING
                   INDISTINCTLY]

05:39.406 --> 05:41.439
              Captain, I am very
                direct person.

05:41.474 --> 05:45.310
       From moment I see you,
     I say, this cat is for me.

05:46.680 --> 05:47.679
          Cat?
              <i> Da.</i>

05:48.448 --> 05:49.948
          Oh. Oh, yes.
             Well--

05:49.983 --> 05:51.015
     Uh, Major Tiomkin, I--

05:51.051 --> 05:53.251
        Sonya, big daddy.

06:03.230 --> 06:05.564
I'm sorry I have to leave you
   alone tonight, Jeannie.

06:05.599 --> 06:06.764
               Oh, I understand.

06:06.800 --> 06:09.301
     You have this Major Tiomkin
           to take care of.

06:09.336 --> 06:11.169
     Yes. Yes,
  I certainly do.

06:11.205 --> 06:12.904
               I would only be
                 in the way.

06:12.939 --> 06:15.740
     You, uh...
  You might, yeah.

06:15.775 --> 06:18.243
We'll probably spend the evening
discussing aerodynamics

06:18.278 --> 06:19.944
  and playing chess.

06:19.979 --> 06:22.280
          Well, I will stay home
           and watch television.

06:22.316 --> 06:24.115
              It is more fun
           than a flying carpet.

06:24.150 --> 06:26.017
  Ah. Good, good.

06:42.069 --> 06:45.003
                Well...off to
            an evening of chess.

06:45.038 --> 06:46.204
  [GIGGLES]

06:46.240 --> 06:47.372
  Master...
                    Yeah?

06:47.407 --> 06:49.574
What does this
Major Tiomkin look like?

06:49.609 --> 06:51.642
              Oh, you know,
         all eyebrows, heavyset.

06:51.678 --> 06:52.877
                Average Russian.

06:55.381 --> 06:57.148
  [JEANNIE'S VOICE]
 Something like this?

06:57.183 --> 06:58.850
                   Yeah.

06:58.885 --> 07:00.118
           Well, yes.

07:00.153 --> 07:02.320
       Uh, he has a little more
           hair than that.

07:04.024 --> 07:05.990
             Uh. Well,
      he doesn't have a beard.

07:07.193 --> 07:08.526
Does he look like this?

07:08.561 --> 07:11.096
  Well, you're getting close,
            but, uh,

07:11.131 --> 07:12.830
            his physique
       is a little different.

07:12.866 --> 07:14.699
     Like this...?

07:15.302 --> 07:16.267
                  Yeah, yeah.

07:16.302 --> 07:17.702
That's more like it, all right.

07:17.737 --> 07:18.703
                   [CHUCKLING]

07:18.739 --> 07:20.772
                Jeannie. Please,
                 I can explain.

07:20.807 --> 07:22.273
Well, there's nothing
to explain.

07:22.309 --> 07:23.541
You have broken your promise.

07:23.576 --> 07:24.843
             N-- I didn't break
                my promise.

07:24.878 --> 07:26.344
               General Barkley
              broke my promise.

07:26.379 --> 07:27.511
               He ordered me
               to take out--

07:27.547 --> 07:28.646
    Play chess?
                    Huh?

07:28.681 --> 07:30.614
Huh. Which one of you
will make the first move?

07:30.650 --> 07:32.583
          He gets his orders
      from the State Department.

07:32.618 --> 07:34.785
       Now, try to understand
   why I have to take out Sonya.

07:34.821 --> 07:37.455
  Mmm!
                 Major Tiomkin.

07:37.490 --> 07:38.589
Of course, master.

07:38.624 --> 07:39.858
  And please try
  to understand

07:39.893 --> 07:41.459
why I must go out
with Captain Healey.

07:41.494 --> 07:43.427
          No-- That's different.
Good night, master.

07:43.463 --> 07:44.495
         You're being childish.

07:44.530 --> 07:46.564
        [DOORBELL RINGS]
        Wait, wait, wait, wait!

07:46.599 --> 07:48.233
            That's, uh..
      That's General Barkley.

07:48.268 --> 07:50.601
At least get back in the bottle
   until he's gone, please.

07:50.636 --> 07:52.003
                Hm, very well.

07:52.038 --> 07:53.771
            I would not want you
                 in trouble.

07:57.010 --> 07:58.276
     Thanks.

07:58.311 --> 08:00.778
Now, if it's not
General Barkley, I'm, uh...

08:00.813 --> 08:02.847
I'm gonna leave you in there
until you cool off.

08:02.883 --> 08:05.550
I'll let you out in...
two or three days.

08:11.558 --> 08:13.424
Would you
cut that out, huh?

08:13.460 --> 08:15.894
[DOORBELL RINGS]

08:17.331 --> 08:18.763
   Oh, hi, Roge.
             Ready for the hands

08:18.798 --> 08:19.764
             across the sea bit?

08:19.799 --> 08:20.798
    TONY:
Uh, yeah. Yup.

08:20.834 --> 08:22.300
             ROGER:
  You better grab a raincoat.

08:22.336 --> 08:24.169
     Cocoa Beach is having
      California weather.

08:24.204 --> 08:25.470
  Oh. All right.

08:25.505 --> 08:26.471
  Oh, boy, I tell you...

08:26.506 --> 08:27.739
   Are you sure you don't have

08:27.774 --> 08:29.840
  Jeannie's phone number
  around here someplace?

08:30.676 --> 08:31.876
  TONY:
Positive.

08:31.912 --> 08:33.244
       ROGER:
You know, on my way here,

08:33.280 --> 08:34.345
I stopped by the library

08:34.381 --> 08:35.513
hoping she'd be there.

08:35.548 --> 08:37.181
I got a feeling
I'm going out of my mind.

08:37.217 --> 08:39.751
TONY:
Look, Roge, you have a little
black book with names

08:39.785 --> 08:41.720
from Abigail to Zelda.
Forget about Jeannie.

08:41.755 --> 08:43.321
           I can't forget her.
           I'm gonna find her

08:43.357 --> 08:44.823
           if I have to spend
           the rest of my life

08:44.858 --> 08:46.591
          standing in front
        of the public library.

08:46.626 --> 08:47.992
   Roge...
      Look, you got the girl.

08:48.027 --> 08:49.394
          You're in a hurry.
                  Yeah.

09:19.859 --> 09:22.460
                It was wonderful
                  night, Tony.

09:22.496 --> 09:24.462
               I wish it could
               go on forever.

09:29.302 --> 09:31.236
  We shake this cube,
      Posnofsky,

09:31.271 --> 09:33.204
and then we really kick it
      around,<i> nyet?</i>

09:33.239 --> 09:34.706
                Well, Sonya, I--

09:34.741 --> 09:36.674
   Ooh! Sly dog.
                      What?

09:36.710 --> 09:39.911
Give me hour, and then we
scooby-dooby at my pad, eh?

09:52.092 --> 09:53.390
            Why did she do that?

09:53.426 --> 09:55.927
Maybe she knew
what I was thinking.

09:55.962 --> 09:56.961
                   Yeah.

10:02.235 --> 10:03.902
Why don't you come in.
We'll have drink.

10:03.937 --> 10:05.136
             <i> Nyet,</i> Sonya.

10:05.172 --> 10:07.405
       Thank you, gentlemen,
      for interesting evening.

10:07.440 --> 10:08.773
              Good night.

10:08.809 --> 10:11.142
   Yeah, as a matter of fact,
I have to be running along too.

10:11.178 --> 10:12.410
                What's the rush?

10:12.445 --> 10:14.312
     Well, I have to look in
     on this friend of mine.

10:14.347 --> 10:16.414
  When I left, uh, this friend
     earlier this evening,

10:16.449 --> 10:17.548
           he was, uh,
          rather upset.

10:17.583 --> 10:19.050
      I'll see you tomorrow.
          Good night.

10:19.086 --> 10:22.420
  Good night, Captain Nelson.

10:29.296 --> 10:32.330
Captain, you have
American cigarette?

10:32.365 --> 10:33.798
                   Amer-American
                     cigarette?

10:34.901 --> 10:36.000
                       [SIGHS]

10:39.406 --> 10:42.474
Oh, it's beautiful
bottle.

10:42.509 --> 10:44.742
     It's-- It's in my raincoat,
      but that's not my bottle.

10:44.778 --> 10:46.611
       It's very unusual.

10:46.646 --> 10:47.878
         You really like it?

10:47.914 --> 10:48.946
              Mm.

10:48.981 --> 10:50.281
               Yours.

10:50.317 --> 10:52.817
         Oh, thank you.

10:52.853 --> 10:55.987
     Wait till I show this
    to my friends in Russia.

10:56.022 --> 10:58.123
You Americans are very generous.

10:59.159 --> 11:00.825
                   Ah! Well,
              I better be going.

11:00.860 --> 11:02.359
               I have to drop in
                at the library.

11:02.395 --> 11:04.062
               I'm looking
         for a friend, and, uh--

11:04.097 --> 11:06.698
Marvelous. I'm very
sleepy myself.

11:06.733 --> 11:09.834
It's been such a long day.

11:09.869 --> 11:12.003
        [YAWNS]

11:27.821 --> 11:29.821
   [SOFT BIG BAND MUSIC PLAYS
           ON STEREO]

11:37.097 --> 11:39.430
            Jeannie.

11:39.465 --> 11:40.698
          Jeannie!

11:41.801 --> 11:43.467
       Look what I brought you.

11:45.504 --> 11:47.004
          Jeannie?

11:48.608 --> 11:50.274
   Where is your bottle?

11:52.378 --> 11:53.377
            Jeannie.

11:53.412 --> 11:54.912
         Now, come on.
      Stop kidding around.

11:54.948 --> 11:57.281
   I-I know you're angry,
           but--

11:57.316 --> 11:59.650
Look, darling, I-I--
I know you're angry at me.

11:59.685 --> 12:03.020
If you'll just come out,
I'll explain everything.

12:03.056 --> 12:05.757
Darling...come out,
wherever you are-- Roger.

12:05.792 --> 12:07.225
         Who are you talking to?
   Nobody.

12:07.260 --> 12:08.425
                 You call nobody
                    "darling"?

12:08.461 --> 12:10.228
I was talking to myself.
You know how it is.

12:10.263 --> 12:11.528
               You call yourself
                   "darling."

12:11.564 --> 12:12.630
            I know you love you,
                    but--

12:12.665 --> 12:13.998
What are you doing
here anyway?

12:14.033 --> 12:15.466
                I figured out
            where you might have

12:15.501 --> 12:16.834
               Jeannie's number.
Forget it!

12:16.870 --> 12:18.936
    Remember when you wrote
   phone numbers on the wall

12:18.972 --> 12:21.305
   beside the kitchen phone?
  That's new wallpaper there.

12:21.340 --> 12:22.640
  We can rip it all off, see.

12:22.675 --> 12:24.642
 I can't rip any wallpaper down.
         I lost a bottle.

12:24.677 --> 12:25.643
 A bottle?
                     A bottle!

12:25.678 --> 12:27.145
That's funny.
I found one tonight.

12:27.180 --> 12:28.179
                        Huh?
                     You what?

12:28.215 --> 12:29.580
    Yeah, it was
  about this high:

12:29.616 --> 12:31.049
Right out of Antiquesville.

12:31.084 --> 12:32.450
          Yeah, yeah. That's it.

12:32.486 --> 12:33.851
Found it
in my raincoat pocket.

12:33.886 --> 12:35.052
                  [SIGHS]
                 Oh, Roge.

12:35.088 --> 12:36.521
           You're a lifesaver.
              Hand it over.

12:36.556 --> 12:38.756
Too late. Sonya liked it,
so I gave it to her.

12:38.791 --> 12:39.757
                You what?

12:39.793 --> 12:41.125
Was there anything wrong there?

12:41.161 --> 12:42.493
      Was there anything wrong?!

12:42.529 --> 12:44.395
      That bottle's in the hands
           of the Russians!

12:45.698 --> 12:47.564
    Whoever has that bottle
      can rule the world.

13:09.722 --> 13:10.721
        Oh, I'm sorry.

13:22.035 --> 13:23.367
                         [KNOCK
                        ON DOOR]

13:30.476 --> 13:32.476
                   I was sure
                 you would come.

13:35.982 --> 13:37.815
I got home, Sonya,
and I said...

13:39.518 --> 13:40.617
why fight it?

13:42.956 --> 13:45.589
                 I do not wish
                   to fight.

13:45.624 --> 13:46.590
  Do you like to dance?

13:46.625 --> 13:48.092
                    Crazy.

13:48.127 --> 13:50.127
  [SLOW BIG BAND MUSIC PLAYING
           ON STEREO]

14:06.379 --> 14:10.615
Tonight is the memory
I take back to Russia.

14:10.650 --> 14:12.850
                I won't forget
                tonight myself.

14:47.487 --> 14:49.721
       You A-okay dancer.

14:54.260 --> 14:56.193
               I improvise
              as I go along.

14:56.229 --> 14:57.862
                 [KNOCK AT DOOR]

14:57.897 --> 15:00.164
      [WHISPERING]
It's probably Posnofsky.

15:01.501 --> 15:02.833
              [CLEARS THROAT]

15:10.109 --> 15:11.408
               Oh, good evening.

15:11.444 --> 15:12.743
        Good evening,
        Major Tiomkin.

15:12.779 --> 15:14.946
     I have tomorrow's
  itinerary here for you.

15:14.981 --> 15:16.346
     Captain Nelson,
     you still here?

15:16.382 --> 15:18.182
             Oh, yes, yes. I was
              just leaving, sir.

15:18.217 --> 15:20.051
        But Captain Nelson,
       you've just come back.

15:20.086 --> 15:21.418
Just come back?
Where were you?

15:21.454 --> 15:23.020
          Sir-- I had to look in
             on a sick friend.

15:23.056 --> 15:24.488
            As a matter of fact,
               I better go see

15:24.523 --> 15:26.290
         how this friend of mine
           is doing right now.

15:26.325 --> 15:27.357
            Oh, please.

15:27.393 --> 15:29.760
       We still have so much
           to talk about.

15:32.698 --> 15:34.598
       Oh, well-- No, I'd really
           better be running.

15:34.634 --> 15:36.567
         This friend of mine
     could kick up quite a fuss.

15:36.602 --> 15:40.404
         But the evening
        is just beginning.

15:40.439 --> 15:41.973
          My bottle.

15:42.008 --> 15:43.241
You're taking
my bottle.

15:43.276 --> 15:44.541
                      Well...
 You took her bottle?

15:44.577 --> 15:45.676
                   Uh, no, sir.
                     No, sir.

15:45.711 --> 15:46.978
                 Captain Healey
                 gave it to her.

15:47.013 --> 15:47.979
                   It's really
                   my bottle.

15:48.014 --> 15:48.980
Well, if it's yours,

15:49.015 --> 15:50.848
I consider it
even more precious gift.

15:50.884 --> 15:51.849
                    [CHUCKLES]
                    Oh, well,

15:51.885 --> 15:53.117
                it's not exactly
                     a gift.

15:53.153 --> 15:54.652
         Give her back
       the bottle, captain.

15:54.687 --> 15:56.553
               I can't, sir. I--
We'll buy you another one.

15:56.589 --> 15:58.856
     Sonya, I'd love to give it,
        but it's an heirloom.

15:58.892 --> 16:00.624
         It's been in the family
             for generations.

16:00.660 --> 16:02.359
You do not come back
to see Sonya.

16:02.395 --> 16:03.928
You come back for bottle.
                        No.

16:03.963 --> 16:06.497
Well, if that's how Americans
treat their guests, keep it.

16:06.532 --> 16:08.099
                 Oh, thank you.
              Thank you so much.

16:09.969 --> 16:12.136
   Give her back the bottle!
                      Oh, sir.

16:12.172 --> 16:13.938
            Our government
      would consider it an honor

16:13.973 --> 16:15.807
   if you would keep the bottle.
          It wouldn't.

16:15.842 --> 16:17.708
          Believe me,
     it wouldn't. I'm not--

16:17.743 --> 16:19.610
     Captain Nelson,
  I'd like a word with you.

16:19.645 --> 16:20.978
           Yes, but--
              Good night, major.

16:21.014 --> 16:23.114
         Sonya-- Major.
              Hey!

16:23.983 --> 16:25.650
          Capitalist!

16:50.076 --> 16:53.010
        They warned me
    about American vodka.

16:53.046 --> 16:55.279
    You are my new mistress,
            master--

16:55.315 --> 16:56.480
    My new master, mistress.

16:56.516 --> 16:58.182
         Oh! It talks.

17:00.686 --> 17:03.353
      I am at your command.
 You may have anything you wish.

17:05.023 --> 17:07.424
        I-I wish I don't
      drink so much vodka.

17:07.459 --> 17:09.859
       Who are you?

17:09.896 --> 17:11.028
                I am your genie.

17:11.064 --> 17:14.198
          Whoever has the bottle
               commands me.

17:14.233 --> 17:16.701
It's practical joke.

17:16.736 --> 17:19.336
                   It is true.

17:19.371 --> 17:21.806
                I can grant you
                   any wish.

17:21.840 --> 17:23.507
   Any wish?

17:28.581 --> 17:30.681
     [TALKING INDISTINCTLY]

17:36.288 --> 17:37.555
   [WHISPERING]
   I test you.

17:37.590 --> 17:41.091
Make Captain Nelson
kick General Barkley.

17:41.127 --> 17:42.092
              Oh, no, master.

17:42.128 --> 17:43.360
             You would not want
                to do that.

17:43.396 --> 17:45.095
    Can you do it?
         Well, of course I can--

17:45.131 --> 17:46.697
        Do it.

17:46.733 --> 17:49.634
             Oh, forgive me,
               ex-master.

17:51.137 --> 17:52.936
       Yes, sir. Doctor,
      you can understand--

17:55.642 --> 17:59.276
     You kicked a general!

17:59.312 --> 18:01.145
          No, no, I didn't, sir.
                 Well, I--

18:01.180 --> 18:03.480
              I-I know it looked
             like I did, but I--

18:03.516 --> 18:05.283
          You see, it's the foot
          at the end of the leg.

18:05.318 --> 18:07.051
            You see, I haven't
         been able to control it

18:07.086 --> 18:08.385
               since I walked
                 in space.

18:08.421 --> 18:09.386
     He did it.

18:09.422 --> 18:10.387
      [GASPS]

18:10.423 --> 18:11.522
   Just so I am sure,

18:11.557 --> 18:13.324
    make him kick
    Dr. Bellows.

18:15.595 --> 18:17.595
              Oh, I'm sorry,
                ex-master.

18:18.698 --> 18:20.297
        ...I was just--

18:22.936 --> 18:24.401
        Well, there goes
        that foot again.

18:25.638 --> 18:27.004
GENERAL:
Dr. Bellows,

18:27.040 --> 18:29.806
  I want you to give this man
a complete examination tomorrow.

18:29.842 --> 18:31.742
And if there's
nothing wrong with him,

18:31.778 --> 18:34.077
        he's mine.
         All mine.

18:34.113 --> 18:35.245
        But, sir, I-I--

18:35.281 --> 18:36.647
    Good night, captain!

18:36.683 --> 18:38.516
              Good night, sir.
              Uh...

18:38.551 --> 18:40.518
              Hm.

18:40.553 --> 18:43.020
        Doctor, I'm sure there's
           an e-explanation--

18:45.158 --> 18:46.324
           Sonya. Hey,
           Sonya, wait.

18:46.359 --> 18:48.159
       Wait a minute, Sonya.

18:48.194 --> 18:50.127
              Hey.

18:50.163 --> 18:51.695
            Let me in, huh?
          I'll tell you what.

18:51.730 --> 18:53.163
           I'll give you $100
            for the bottle.

18:53.199 --> 18:55.299
                    [KNOCKING]
               Sonya? Let me in.

18:55.334 --> 18:56.801
          You can do anything?

18:56.836 --> 18:58.469
     Anything.
                           TONY:
                          Major!

18:58.505 --> 19:00.505
                  Oh, boy,
             are we in business.

19:06.913 --> 19:07.912
          Yes, thank you.

19:07.947 --> 19:09.613
             [SNIFFS]

19:11.383 --> 19:13.718
     What do you mean, she's
    on her way to the airport?

19:13.753 --> 19:16.353
  Major Tiomkin wasn't scheduled
      to leave until tonight.

19:16.388 --> 19:19.123
 Sergeant, why wasn't I informed
   about this change in plans?

19:19.158 --> 19:20.224
              Huh?

19:20.259 --> 19:22.326
     All right, all right.
          Never mind.

19:22.361 --> 19:23.994
             Jeannie...
          wherever you are,

19:24.030 --> 19:27.264
if you can do any moonlighting,
 grant me this one last favor.

19:27.299 --> 19:29.734
 Get me to the airport on time.

19:29.769 --> 19:30.735
                        Sir.

19:30.770 --> 19:31.836
  Now, captain,

19:31.871 --> 19:34.705
you and I are going to
have a nice, long talk.

19:34.741 --> 19:36.173
                Could we talk
            a little later, sir?

19:36.209 --> 19:37.374
   I'm on my way
  to the airport.

19:37.409 --> 19:41.678
             You're on your way
             to a court-martial.

19:41.714 --> 19:45.049
               Unless I have
          your full cooperation.

19:45.084 --> 19:48.085
         Now...let's start
         at the beginning.

19:48.854 --> 19:50.187
                    As you know,
                      captain,

19:50.223 --> 19:52.489
  I've had you under observation
        for several months.

19:52.525 --> 19:54.524
  I'll only be an hour, sir.
     I'll be right back.

19:54.560 --> 19:57.194
      To date, you've had
        hallucinations,

19:57.230 --> 19:59.262
                    you've heard
                      voices...

19:59.298 --> 20:02.499
     And now you seem to have
         a bottle fetish.

20:02.535 --> 20:04.201
                   For all these
                      things,

20:04.236 --> 20:06.203
              you've had dubious
                explanations.

20:06.238 --> 20:07.204
         Half an hour?

20:07.240 --> 20:09.373
  But there is no explanation

20:09.409 --> 20:10.941
 for striking a fellow officer.

20:10.977 --> 20:12.509
     No. I know that, sir.

20:12.545 --> 20:15.879
           That is the ultimate
         in irrational behavior.

20:15.914 --> 20:16.980
    I know that.

20:18.384 --> 20:19.650
     Bless you.

20:19.685 --> 20:21.685
You better watch
that foot, doctor.

20:41.640 --> 20:44.308
Flight 439 to Berlin.
Has it taken off yet?

20:44.343 --> 20:45.576
                 There she goes.

20:52.551 --> 20:54.584
           We've lost.

20:54.620 --> 20:55.886
  The Russians have the bottle.

21:07.066 --> 21:08.966
            [SIGHS]

21:09.001 --> 21:11.335
      Roger, will you forget
          about Jeannie?

21:11.370 --> 21:14.438
             N-- I mean,
       just consider her gone.

21:14.473 --> 21:16.407
                No.
        I mean, really gone.

21:16.442 --> 21:18.042
            For good.
[DOORBELL RINGS]

21:18.077 --> 21:20.444
   There's somebody at the door.
     I-I'll talk to you later.

21:25.217 --> 21:26.216
    Yes, miss.

21:28.687 --> 21:29.687
Sonya.

21:30.957 --> 21:35.325
         Formerly Sonya Tiomkin.
             Now Betsy Ross.

21:36.395 --> 21:39.163
   Oh. Betsy Ross?
                   Yes.

21:39.198 --> 21:43.233
         This bottle made me
     what I always wanted to be:

21:43.269 --> 21:45.502
               wealthy American.

21:45.538 --> 21:47.838
Ah. I think I understand.

21:47.874 --> 21:51.308
Well. Well,
welcome aboard, Betsy.

21:51.343 --> 21:52.976
I-I can guess
why you're here.

21:53.012 --> 21:54.244
 You have everything you want,

21:54.279 --> 21:56.246
     and you want to return
       the bottle, right?

21:56.281 --> 21:57.881
               Yes, it's true.

21:57.917 --> 22:01.819
    I have villa on the Riviera,
     a mansion in Beverly Hills.

22:01.854 --> 22:05.322
        My chauffeur's waiting
      outside in my Rolls Royce.

22:05.357 --> 22:07.191
                But that's not
              everything I want.

22:07.226 --> 22:08.759
 Yeah-- What else is there?

22:08.794 --> 22:10.594
                You.

22:10.629 --> 22:11.962
        Wh-- Me?

22:11.997 --> 22:13.197
           I'll make you a deal.

22:13.232 --> 22:15.332
                You marry me,
              I give you bottle.

22:15.367 --> 22:17.467
          Uh...
      Ma-marry you?

22:17.503 --> 22:19.269
          Well--
 Well, I can't marry you.

22:19.304 --> 22:23.006
I mean, uh-- Well, I want
Jeannie back desperately,

22:23.041 --> 22:24.742
but marriage
is out of the question.

22:24.777 --> 22:26.844
                Too bad.
           You, me and bottle

22:26.879 --> 22:28.312
could have had the world.

22:28.347 --> 22:29.747
              Yeah, please, uh--

22:29.782 --> 22:33.150
             At least, may I say
             goodbye to Jeannie?

22:33.186 --> 22:35.285
     Why not.
  But no tricks.

22:35.321 --> 22:36.386
                   All right.
                   No tricks.

22:42.361 --> 22:44.127
Oh, ex-master,
darling.

22:44.163 --> 22:45.963
I thought I would
never see you again.

22:45.998 --> 22:48.065
     I thought I'd never see you
        again either, Jeannie.

22:48.100 --> 22:49.733
  There's so much I want to say.

22:49.768 --> 22:51.869
      Oh, there's so much
        I want to hear.

22:51.904 --> 22:55.706
                 Uh, Betsy--
                    Sonya.

22:55.741 --> 22:58.775
            May I, uh, speak to
          Jeannie alone, please?

22:58.811 --> 23:00.177
          All right.

23:00.213 --> 23:02.112
          But I keep
         bottle here.

23:02.148 --> 23:03.314
              Hurry it up.

23:03.349 --> 23:05.082
             I want her tell me
           who wins daily double

23:05.117 --> 23:06.683
           at Hialeah tomorrow.
    Yeah.

23:19.898 --> 23:21.598
              I'm gonna miss you
              terribly, Jeannie.

23:21.633 --> 23:23.434
Oh, and I'm going to
miss you, master.

23:25.304 --> 23:28.639
          I never realized
   just how much I missed you...

23:28.674 --> 23:29.640
          until this happened.

23:29.675 --> 23:31.341
You would like me to stay?

23:31.376 --> 23:34.011
                Of course I w--

23:34.046 --> 23:35.012
            You mean, you could?

23:35.047 --> 23:36.680
    If she frees me.

23:36.715 --> 23:39.416
                 Well, you heard
                  what she said.

23:39.452 --> 23:42.453
                 She's not gonna
                 free you, and--

23:42.488 --> 23:43.754
              I can't marry her,
                   Jeannie.

23:43.789 --> 23:46.023
If you want to
keep me, you must.

23:54.433 --> 23:57.468
Sonya...I've
changed my mind.

23:57.503 --> 24:00.570
If you haven't changed yours,
I'll marry you.

24:00.606 --> 24:04.608
           Darling. I'm going to
            make you very happy.

24:06.479 --> 24:07.811
 We'll fly to Mexico.

24:07.846 --> 24:09.179
  We'll be married
   before sunup.

24:09.215 --> 24:10.947
             Oh, wonderful!

24:10.983 --> 24:12.749
    And we can leave
      that there.

24:12.784 --> 24:15.519
              Anything you say,
                darling. Oh.

24:24.230 --> 24:25.429
                Stay there.

24:30.269 --> 24:31.902
             What's gonna happen
              when she finds out

24:31.937 --> 24:33.103
               she's married
               a phony Tony?

24:33.139 --> 24:36.006
Oh, I do not care,
master, darling.

24:36.042 --> 24:37.974
   As long as I have
     the real one.

24:38.010 --> 24:39.076
             [CHUCKLING]

24:43.482 --> 24:46.683
             [♪♪♪]
